# Project rules for Cline

## CI / GitHub Workflows

- **DO NOT add or modify files under `.github/workflows/`.**
  The current Git Personal Access Token (PAT) does **not** have the `workflow`
  scope, so any push that touches a workflow file is rejected by GitHub:
  > refusing to allow a Personal Access Token to create or update workflow
  > `.github/workflows/<file>` without `workflow` scope

  Until a token with `workflow` scope is available, keep all CI/automation
  out of `.github/workflows/`. If CI guidance is needed, document it in
  `README.md` or `docs/` as a suggested snippet the user can add manually,
  rather than committing the file.